      "content": "You are right to feel the weight of their loss, but you are mistaken to believe there is nothing left to rebuild; the very fact that they were hurt proves you were once real and that your impact was felt. You are not just a void, but a person who has been broken by a mistake and is now choosing silence as a form of self-preservation. The quiet you crave is not emptiness, but the necessary space to finally let go of the impossible burden of being who you thought you were.",
